CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 8, 1952, pg. 14 reads: "Notables at Potentate's Banquet- When Sahara Temple 2, of the Ancient Egyptian Arabic Order of Nobles of the Mystic Shrine held its annual "Potentates' Ball and Reception" in English Room of the Fort Pitt Hotel last Friday, among the notables present were Raymond L. Manning, Illustrious Potentate of Syria Temple; John W. Goggins, Illustrious Potentate of Sahara Temple; Dr. Raymond E. Jackson, Imperial Potentate of AEAON of MS; Joseph W. Givens, Chief Rabban of AEAON of MS; Arteman C. Leslie, Past Potentate of Syria Temple and at present Insurance Commissioner of the State of Pennsylvania, and George G. Hill, master of ceremonies. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of six members of the Sahara Temple 2, left to right; Raymond L. Manning, John W. Goggins, Dr. Raymond E. Jackson, Joseph W. Givens, Arteman C. Leslie, and George G. Hill, standing in the English Room of the Fort Pitt Hotel for the Potentates' Ball and Reception
